<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> Smith, Richard Gordon, <a href="http://www.sacred-texts.com/shi/atfj/atfj51.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.sacred-texts.com/shi/atfj/atfj51.htm" rel="nofollow">"The Snow Ghost"</a> Chapter XLIX of <i>Ancient Tales and Folk-lore of Japan</i> at <a href="http://www.sacred-texts.com/index.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.sacred-texts.com/index.htm" rel="nofollow">sacred-texts.com</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-b-5">^ <a href="#cite_ref-b_5-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-b_5-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="http://www.sarudama.com/japanese_folklore/kwaidan_-_yuki-.shtml" class="external text" title="http://www.sarudama.com/japanese_folklore/kwaidan_-_yuki-.shtml" rel="nofollow">Kwaidan - Yuki-onna (Snow Woman)</a> at <a href="http://www.sarudama.com" class="external text" title="http://www.sarudama.com" rel="nofollow">www.sarudama.com</a></li>
</ol>
